<TITLE> Direct trains from Jessore, Khulna to Cantonment station by early Aug </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kamran Reza Chowdhury bdnews24.com Senior Correspondent Dhaka, July 21 (bdnews24.com)  People from Khulna and Jessore can come to the capital by first week of August as Bangladesh Railway (BR) is going to start a direct train service from Dhaka Cantonment Station instead of Joydevpur, a railway official said Saturday. Again, the BR may introduce another new passenger train on Dhaka-Khulna route soon. "We hope that by first week of August passenger trains will be operate from Cantonment station instead of Joydevpur," Kazi Asad Ullah, additional director general, operations, told bdnews24.com Saturday. The ADG said the officials would meet on Sunday and Thursday at the Railway Bhaban to discuss the introduction of direct passenger train service between Dhaka and Khulna. "We are planning to introduce another train on the route," Asad Ullah said and added a final decision would come from Sunday's meeting. If everything goes as planned, Sundarban Express can come up to Joydevpur station, some 30 kilometres off the capital, starting from Southwestern districts of Khulna and Jessore. A pair of shuttle trains now run to carry passengers to and from Joydevpur and Komalapur stations. With Joydevpur-Cantonment rail tracks made dual-gauge, the broad-gauge trains from Jessore and Khulna will be able to reach Cantonment station, the official said. Railway officials said about 1,500 passengers travel by the Sundarban Express every day. bdn
